100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 30, 1925, the world witnessed significant political developments as France announced plans to strengthen its military presence in the Rhineland amidst rising tensions in Europe. In the United States, the ongoing debates on Prohibition intensified, with numerous states grappling with enforcement challenges and public sentiment shifting. Meanwhile, in the realm of science, the discovery of a new species of dinosaur was reported, sparking excitement in paleontological circles.
